President Donald Trump has announced the designation of a Presidential Delegation to Mexico City to attend the Presidential Inauguration of President Andrés Manuel López Obrador on December 1, 2018. The delegation will be led by Vice President Mike Pence and includes Second Lady Karen Pence, Secretary of Energy Rick Perry, Secretary of Homeland Security Kirstjen Nielsen, Assistant to the President Ivanka Trump, Chargé d’Affaires John S. Creamer, and Counselor of the Department T. Ulrich Brechbühl.